name: ammonium nitrate phosphate production | ammonium nitrate phosphate | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/23765/documentation

This dataset is a weighted average from the respective regional datasets.;This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of ammonium nitrate phosphate (ANP) with 22% N and 22% P2O5 from ammonia and rock phosphate. ANP is a compound fertiliser used to enrich the soil in nitrogen (N) and phosphorous (P), two of the main macronutrients needed to support plant growth.;The production of ammonium nitrate phosphate involves the combination of liquid ammonia with nitric acid and rock phosphate, using heat and electricity. Production and waste treatment of catalysts, coating and packaging of the final fertiliser product are excluded. Infrastructure is included by means of a proxy module.;The main data sources for this dataset are Patyk and Reinhardt (1997) and Althaus et al (2007).;References:;Patyk A. and Reinhardt G. (1997) Düngemittel - Energie- und Strombilanzen. Vieweg Verlag. Braunschweig/Wiesbaden.;Althaus H.-J., Chudacoff M., Hischier R., Jungbluth N., Osses M. and Primas A. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 8, v2.0. EMPA Dübendorf, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH.

The activity includes all the raw and processed materials necessary to produce this product. Liquid ammonia, nitric acid, rock phosphate, heat (as natural gas) and electricity are included. Direct emissions include ammonia, nitrogen oxides and particulate matter to air and heavy metals to water.

The activity ends with the final product being ready for transportation at the production site.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2012:Manufacture of fertilizers and nitrogen compounds

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Primary data were collected on fertiliser production for the year 2013-2014. These data were based on annual average data based on different production plants.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: RER, RNA, CN.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Average techlogy from the regional counterparts as given in the geography comment.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription:
This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.  Weights are based on production volumes.
RER: production volume = 3.76e+08 kg/year, weight = 0.4282
RNA: production volume = 3.26e+08 kg/year, weight = 0.3713
CN: production volume = 1.76e+08 kg/year, weight = 0.2004
